1. exstiterit. . . ait: Ι see no reason whatever for changing sit of the MSS. into crit with Bake, Kayser, and Sorof, and taking exstiterit as fut perf. ind. It is quite natural to regard the appearance of an ideal orator as a more imaginary and unreal hypothesis than the dispute of a practised orator with a mere philosopher ; hence verberabit need not determine the construction of the next clause.
